title: Trump's three trips to Mar-a-Lago rack up $10million bill
text: show ad Trump's three trips to Mar-a-Lago rack up $10million bill - same as the cost for a YEAR of running Camp David As the president hits the one-month mark in office, he's likely spent $10 million in taxpayer dollars on travel to his private club in Florida thus far A critic of President Obama's vacations, Trump will likely cost as much as the Democrat did in eight years, by the end of 2017 Trump has chosen to spend his weekends away from Washington in Florida, instead of at Camp David, which costs taxpayers $10 million a year to run Published: 22:37 GMT, 21 February 2017 | Updated: 00:38 GMT, 22 February 2017 92 shares
